{
  "stem": "24259.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember, I've always liked dogs.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And having him at that time was very comforting for me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I believe so, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Probably close to a year, from the time after we were liberated to the time that we went through Bytom-- our stay at Bytom.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I guess they just got rid of him or gave him away to somebody.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I really don't remember, specifically, what happened to him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I-- I think, you know, in retrospect, certainly we were very, very lucky.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was-- I guess, the only way to describe it is it's like a miracle, certain events happening and not happening, that meant us being survivors and us being killed with the others.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was just pure-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] [LAUGHS] just pure luck or-- or just a special kind of sense that my father had-- instinct, if you will-- to do certain things, or certain things happening, that kept us alive.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think it's just the only way to describe it is like a miracle.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Certain things that I-- my father and my parents, over the years, have talked about, and certain things that would happen at certain times.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were pure coincidences that meant us surviving and not surviving.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Recently, my father at this time always observes the time of death-- it's called Yahrzeit-- for those that got killed.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And specifically, within this last couple of weeks, we observed the Yahrzeit of my mother's side of the family that managed to escape from the ghetto, and they were also hiding out on a farm of the Gentiles.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And at one time-- this was even before our first place of hiding.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was just a transition [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] place where we hid out in a barn in the straw.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
